There will be no change to the rights and status of EU nationals living in the UK, nor UK nationals living in the EU, while the UK remains in the EU.
The 2018 FIFA World Cup is taking place in Russia from 14 June to 15 July. The FCO has put together some top travel and safety tips to help fans travelling to Russia for the tournament. See Be on the Ball. If you intend to travel from Latvia to Kaliningrad via Lithuania or Poland, you should additionally check our travel advice for Lithuania and Poland before you travel.
Terrorist attacks in Latvia can’t be ruled out. See Terrorism
Around 142,000 British nationals visit Latvia each year. Most visits are trouble-free.
If you’re abroad and you need emergency help from the UK government, contact the nearest British embassy, consulate or high commission.
Take out comprehensive travel and medical insurance before you travel.
